    <name>
      <text>Calculating average speed with time segment</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A cyclist travels at {@s1@} km/h for {@t1@} hours, then at {@s2@} km/h for {@t2@} hours.</p>
<p>Calculate the average speed for the entire journey.</p>

<p>Average speed = [[input:ans1]] km/h [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p><strong>Step 1: Calculate distance for each segment</strong><br>
First segment: Distance = Speed × Time = \( {@s1@} \times {@t1@} = {@d1@} \) km<br>
Second segment: Distance = Speed × Time = \( {@s2@} \times {@t2@} = {@d2@} \) km</p>

<p><strong>Step 2: Calculate total distance and total time</strong><br>
Total distance = {@d1@} + {@d2@} = {@d1+d2@} km<br>
Total time = {@t1@} + {@t2@} = {@t1+t2@} hours</p>

<p><strong>Step 3: Calculate average speed</strong><br>
Therefore, average speed is given by:<br>  \( \begin{align} =& \frac{\text{Total distance}}{\text{Total time}}\\=& \frac{{@total_distance@}}{{@total_time@}}\\\ =& {@ta@}\,\, \text{km/h} \end{align} \) </p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
